    <title>Fourth statement of new regulation of 'one-in, one-out’ regime </title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Overview of regulations planned to be implemented or removed by government departments between 1 July and 31 December 2012.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;A forward look of all regulations in scope of government’s ‘one-in, one-out’ regime that are scheduled to come into force between 1 July and 31 December 2012.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is published every 6 months to give businesses an indication of when regulations affecting them will be coming into effect.
The headline figures show the measures that will be introduced this year that are expected to reduce burdens on businesses by an estimated £0.3 million per year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It provides an overview of the net costs and benefits to business and civil society organisations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
